mlflex.ensemblelearners
Class AbstractEnsembleLearner

java.lang.Object
  mlflex.ensemblelearners.AbstractEnsembleLearner
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractWeightedVoteEnsembleLearner, MajorityVoteEnsembleLearner, MaxProbabilityEnsembleLearner, MeanProbabilityEnsembleLearner, SelectBestEnsembleLearner, StackedEnsembleLearner
public abstract class AbstractEnsembleLearner
extends java.lang.Object

ML-Flex supports ensemble-learning approaches for aggregating evidence from multiple classification predictions. This class is a generic handler of all ensemblelearners approaches in ML-Flex.

Author:
Stephen Piccolo

MakeEnsemblePredictions

public java.lang.Boolean MakeEnsemblePredictions(int outerFold,
                                                 java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,EnsemblePredictionInfos> ensemblePredictionInfoMap)
                                          throws java.lang.Exception
This method is the workhorse of this class. Having received information about individual predictions that were made for each data instance, it combines the individual predictions into a combined prediction, using the custom logic of the overriding class.

Parameters:
outerFold - Number of outer cross-validation fold
ensemblePredictionInfoMap - Map of ensemblelearners prediction info (one for each data instance)
Returns:
Indicates whether this method was successful
Throws:
java.lang.Exception
